In rectangle $ABCD$, $AB=5$ and $BC =3$. Points $F$ and $G$ are on $\overline{CD}$ so that $DF = 1$ and $GC=2$. Lines $AF$ and $BG$ intersect at $E$. Find the area of $\triangle AEB$. Express your answer as a common fraction. [asy]
pair A,B,C,D,I,F,G;
A=(0,0);
B=(5,0);
C=(5,3);
D=(0,3);
F=(1,3);
G=(3,3);
I=(1.67,5);
draw(A--B--C--D--cycle,linewidth(0.7));
draw(A--B--I--cycle,linewidth(0.7));
label("$A$",A,SW);
label("$B$",B,SE);
label("$C$",C,NE);
label("$D$",D,NW);
label("$F$",F,SE);
label("$G$",G,SW);
label("$E$",I,N);
label("1",(0.5,3),N);
label("2",(4,3),N);
label("3",(0,1.5),W);
label("3",(5,1.5),E);
label("5",(2.5,0),S);
[/asy]

Squares $ABCD$ and $EFGH$ are equal in area.  Vertices $B$, $E$, $C$, and $H$ lie on the same line.  Diagonal $AC$ is extended to $J$, the midpoint of $GH$.  What is the fraction of the two squares that is shaded? [asy]
fill((0,4)--(4,4)--(4,0)--cycle,gray);
fill((4,0)--(6,0)--(6,-2)--cycle,gray);
draw((0,0)--(4,0)--(4,4)--(0,4)--cycle,linewidth(1));
draw((2,0)--(6,0)--(6,-4)--(2,-4)--cycle,linewidth(1));
draw((0,4)--(6,-2),linewidth(1));
label("$A$",(0,4),NW);
label("$B$",(0,0),W);
label("$C$",(4,0),NE);
label("$D$",(4,4),NE);
label("$E$",(2,0),SW);
label("$F$",(2,-4),SW);
label("$G$",(6,-4),SE);
label("$H$",(6,0),E);
label("$J$",(6,-2),E);
[/asy]

In the diagram, $K$, $O$ and $M$ are the centers of the three semi-circles. Also, $OC = 32$ and $CB = 36$.

[asy]
pair A, K, O, C, M, B, X, Y, Z;
O=(0,0);
C=(32,0);
M=(50,0);
B=(68,0);
A=(-68,0);
K=(A+C)/2;
X=(0,68);
Y=(-18,50);
Z=(50,18);
path nom, bigc, middlec, smallc;
nom=A--B--(100,100)--(-100,100)--cycle;
bigc=A..X..B--cycle;
middlec=A..Y..C--cycle;
smallc=C..Z..B--cycle;
fill(bigc, gray(.5));
fill(middlec, white);
fill(smallc, white);
draw(smallc);
draw(middlec);
draw(bigc);
draw(A--B);
label("A", A, S);
label("K", K, S);
label("O", O, S);
label("M", M, S);
label("C", C, S);
label("B", B, S);
dot(K);
dot(O);
dot(M);
[/asy]

